es/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/ak/batch_ak_kodiakriverotter_ver02/data/sn95060049/00513680053/1910063001/0187.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn95060049/1910-06-30/ed-1/?sp=4"], "batch": ["ak_kodiakriverotter_ver02"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/alaska/", "3/united states/alaska/tanana/"], "contributor": ["alaska state library historical collections"], "date": "1910-06-30", "dates": ["1910-06-30"], "description": ["HOTEL ACCOMMODATIONS ARE BEINC IMPROVED When the improvements now under way and under immediate contempla tion are completed there will no longer j be any room for complaint that Tanana does not possess adequate hotel accom modations The towns central location makes it a stopping place for all classes of people who have occasion to travel in interior Alaska Nothing is more calculated to give a had impression of a place than poor and forbidding hotels and Tananas hotels have not been up to a very high standard The condition was fully rec ognized and is being speedily and ef fectually remedied The Tower House Joe Anicich was one of the first to make a move for betterment and the result is the Tower House a hotel that would be creditable to a city of several thousand people The rooms of this fine place have just been opened to the public and are the perfection of comfort and repose High ceilings generous size wide halls every arrangement was made with the object in view of afford ing a thorough ventilation Steam heat and sanitary plumbing will be installed as quickly as circumstances will permit and every appointment of the establish"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2024-05-22T13:01:31.040Z", "group": ["ndnp/ak", "alaska-state-library-historical-collections-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn95060049/1910-06-30/ed-1/?sp=4", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/serv